---
title: Sponsors - PyCon India 2025
description: Sponsor PyCon India 2025 and support the Python community
layout: base.njk
---

{% from "components/button.njk" import button %}
{% from "components/window.njk" import window %}
<div class="w-full h-auto bg-pycon-blue -mb- px-[10%] pt-[200px]">
    <div class="flex flex-col md:flex-row">
        <div class="pb-8 md:pb-16 w-full lg:w-[70%]">
            <div class="black-han-sans-regular font-normal text-3xl md:text-5xl md:text-center text-[#FFFFFF] text-center lg:text-left">
                Why Sponsor?
            </div>
            <div class="text-md lg:text-xl pt-12 text-[#FFFFFF] lg:pr-20 pb-64">
                <p>PyCon India 2025 is back in Bengaluru, Karnataka, allowing our community to come together to network, learn, share
                    ideas, and create new relationships and partnerships.</p>
                <p class="pt-4">Your sponsorship helps us make PyCon India accessible to developers from diverse backgrounds and
                    supports the growth of the Python community in India.</p>
                <p class="pt-4">We invite you to be a part of this vibrant community and showcase your brand at the largest Python
                    conference in India. Join us in making PyCon India 2025 a success and help shape the future of Python in India!</p>
                <p class="pt-4">As a sponsor, you will have the opportunity to connect with a diverse audience of Python enthusiasts,
                    developers, and industry leaders. Your support will not only enhance your brand visibility but also contribute to the
                    growth and sustainability of the Python community in India. We offer a range of sponsorship packages to suit your needs,
                    from title sponsorship to community support. Each package is designed to provide maximum exposure and engagement
                    opportunities for your brand.</p>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="relative pl-8 lg:pl-16">
            <img src="{{ env.baseUrl }}img/assets/sponsors.svg" alt="Sponsors" class="w-full block w-[100%] lg:w-[100%]">
            <img src="{{ env.baseUrl }}img/assets/star-pink-vector.svg" alt="Groovy star" class="absolute right-16 top-[18.5rem] w-[25%] lg:w-[15%] animate-bounce-slow">
            <img src="{{ env.baseUrl }}img/assets/circle-lavender.svg" alt="Circle Lavender" class="absolute right-[14rem] top-[29rem] w-full lg:w-auto animate-bounce-fast">
            <img src="{{ env.baseUrl }}img/assets/tetris.svg" alt="Tetris" class="absolute w-40 md:w-8 lg:w-20 right-32 bottom-[18rem] rotate-12 animate-bounce-slower">
            <img src="{{ env.baseUrl }}img/assets/ellipse-lime.svg" alt="Ellipse Lime" class="absolute w-full lg:w-auto right-0 bottom-[25rem] animate-bounce-slowest">
            <img src="{{ env.baseUrl }}img/assets/circle-lavender.svg" alt="Circle Lavender" class="absolute w-full lg:w-auto right-0 bottom-[18rem] animate-bounce-slow">
        </div>
    </div>
</div>
<div class="relative">
    <div class="absolute left-[10%] right-[10%] -top-40 z-10 flex flex-col lg:flex-row items-start">
        <div class="text-md lg:text-xl font-light flex-1">
            {% call window(width=800, height=500, depth=25, frontBg="lavender", leftBg="lime", topBg="lime") %}
                <span class="font-semibold text-black">What you can expect when you sponsor PyCon India:</span>
                <ul class="list-none space-y-4 mt-4">
                    <li class="flex items-start">
                        <div class="w-4 h-4 bg-pycon-lime rounded-full mr-4 mt-1 flex-shrink-0 border-2 border-green-600"></div>
                        <div>
                            <span class="font-semibold text-gray-800">Reach</span>
                            <span class="text-gray-600"> - Access to 2,500+ attendees interested in your products and services and generate qualified leads.</span>
                        </div>
                    </li>
                    <li class="flex items-start">
                        <div class="w-4 h-4 bg-pycon-lime rounded-full mr-4 mt-1 flex-shrink-0 border-2 border-green-600"></div>
                        <div>
                            <span class="font-semibold text-gray-800">Brand strength</span>
                            <span class="text-gray-600"> - Being part of the biggest and most prestigious Python conference in the world and supporting the nonprofit organization behind the Python language.</span>
                        </div>
                    </li>
                    <li class="flex items-start">
                        <div class="w-4 h-4 bg-pycon-lime rounded-full mr-4 mt-1 flex-shrink-0 border-2 border-green-600"></div>
                        <div>
                            <span class="font-semibold text-gray-800">Connections</span>
                            <span class="text-gray-600"> - Networking with attendees in person to create connections and provide detailed information about your products and services.</span>
                        </div>
                    </li>
                    <li class="flex items-start">
                        <div class="w-4 h-4 bg-pycon-lime rounded-full mr-4 mt-1 flex-shrink-0 border-2 border-green-600"></div>
                        <div>
                            <span class="font-semibold text-gray-800">Recruiting</span>
                            <span class="text-gray-600"> - Access to qualified job candidates. If you're hiring, there's no better place to find Python developers than PyCon India.</span>
                        </div>
                    </li>
                    <li class="flex items-start">
                        <div class="w-4 h-4 bg-pycon-lime rounded-full mr-4 mt-1 flex-shrink-0 border-2 border-green-600"></div>
                        <div>
                            <span class="font-semibold text-gray-800">12 months of benefits</span>
                            <span class="text-gray-600"> - Reach the Python community during PyCon India and beyond, with options for recognition on <a href="https://python.org" class="text-blue-600 underline">Python.org</a>, <a href="https://pypi.org" class="text-blue-600 underline">PyPI.org</a>, and more.</span>
                        </div>
                    </li>
                </ul>
            {% endcall %}
        </div>
        <div class="relative flex items-end gap-0 mt-16">
            {# <img src="{{ env.baseUrl }}img/assets/bench.svg" alt="Bench" class="w-auto h-20 lg:h-24">
            <img src="{{ env.baseUrl }}img/assets/tree-1.svg" alt="Tree" class="w-auto h-32 lg:h-40 -ml-4">
            <img src="{{ env.baseUrl }}img/assets/tree-1.svg" alt="Tree" class="w-auto h-32 lg:h-40 -ml-4">
            <img src="{{ env.baseUrl }}img/assets/fence.svg" alt="Fence" class="absolute right-0 bottom-0 w-auto h-24 lg:h-32"> #}
        </div>
    </div>
    <div class="main-container pt-96 bg-lavender w-full h-auto px-[6%] pb-40 md:pb-60 lg:pb-[20%]">
    </div>
</div>